7380159126610988296: Experience the allure of 19th-century Madrid at Hotel Santo Mauro, once the residence of the influential Duke of Santo Mauro.  Immerse yourself in French-inspired design across three historic buildings nestled within a refined private garden adorned with fountains and shaded terraces by ancient chestnut trees.  This 5-star hotel intricately weaves historical references into its guest rooms, each exuding unique charm.  From the elegant French Classicism of the Red Room to the exotic allure of the Chinese Lounge, reminiscent of the Duke's worldly collections, every public space tells a story.  Indulge in an extensive wine selection and delectable small dishes at the Wine Bar, or savor palatial cuisine in the former Library-turned-main restaurant.  Enriched with music, fresh blooms, and impeccable service, a stay at the palace promises an unforgettable journey through time. #oldmoneyaesthetic #16thcenturyaesthetic #romanticizinglife #oldmoney #oldsoul #oldmoneycentury #fyp #elegantstyle

You can purchase bus tickets at the local “tabacchi” originally a store for cigarettes and tobacco related items but it’s actually a small convenience store. I missed the bus and had to wait 2 HOURS for the next one so I hiked a mountain for like 2-3 hours so don’t do that lol  3-  Visit the attraction early! This gets packed really quickly specifically in July and August and gets super crowded! If you plan to visit, it’s better to go in the morning around 10AM.  Have you been to the Amalfi Coast before?? Olive oil Salt Onion 5 stalks of celery 4 carrots Garlic Cumin powder Turmeric powder Black pepper Sage powder Bay leaves Rosemary Cayenne pepper Chicken bone broth 2x chicken breasts Italian parsley Sauté onion then add diced celery and carrot with garlic Then add 1 litre chicken bone broth Add turmeric, cayenne pepper, cumin, sage, rosemary, peppers, bay leaves, rosemary Bring to boil Add 4 cups of boiling water Add handful of parsley Then add 2 chicken breasts Boil for 30 mins Take out a chicken breast and cut to see if it’s cooked through Add fusilli pasta Use tongs to shred chicken breast Add chicken back in once pasta is cooked Add parsley let it simmer until you think it’s ready to serve! #chickennoodle #selfcareroutine #selfcaretips #holistichealing #holisticnutrition #chickennoodlesoup #bonebroth #pinterestaesthetic #asmr

7464740533190217006: #1 They set goals. Successful women know the importance of goal setting and implementation. They consistently set goals on a weekly, monthly, annual basis and measure how they perform over time. #2 They prioritize. If you try to do everything at the same time, you won’t get anything done. It’s better to do 2-3 tasks with 100% efficiency instead of trying to do 10 tasks with 20% efficiency. #3 They network. Building your network and connecting with like-minded women will get you faster to manifest your dreams. You don’t need to have 100 close friends, but it is important to have a network of people professionally and personally that you can fall back on. #4 They know when to take time off. As a successful woman, you KNOW you will always have more things to do than time to do them. Nevertheless, women who are high-achievers prioritize “me time” and take time off. Whether it’s getting that mani-pedi, a new haircut or just taking your family and friends to lunch, nothing beats downtime. #5 They ask for what they want. Nobody ever achieved success by being a “yes woman.” Women who are killing it are also the ones who face their fears and speak up. They stand up and ask for a salary increase, feedback, and ways to improve their work and get ahead. You can’t just “hope” success will come your way. You need to show up and ask for it. #6 They are consistent. Instead of putting in one hour one day and then 14 the next, and then forgetting all about their dream, they work CONSISTENTLY on their goals and achieve them. #7 They don’t expect overnight results. Great things take time. Success takes a lot of hard work, patience, sacrifice, consistency, discipline, self-confidence, faith, and many more things but this is the price that you pay for success. So if you’d like to be successful, understand that it is a process and not an instant manifestation. #BossLadyMindset #Success #SuccessfulWomen #HabitsOfSuccess #AlphaWomanEnergy #UnstoppableWomen #SuccessMindset #LevelUp #ManifestYourDreams

7378565322053340449: Taking time off is to intentionally stop work, social media, a hobby, or whatever you want to take time off from in order to rest and prioritize your health. 7309164065484672302: So comforting and continues to get better the next day 💌 Irish beef stew recipe ⬇️ 3lb chuck beef  Onion Garlic  Celery  Carrots Crushed tomato  Red wine  Beef stock + 1 cup water Golden gourmet potatoes  Rosemary  Parsley  Sage, 2 bay leaves  Celtic sea salt  Pepper  Sear chuck beef on each side at a high heat seasoning with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Remove and cut up.  Cook onions, celery, carrots, add rosemary, parsley, sage, 2 bay leaves, Celtic sea salt for 5 mins. Add crushed tomato, red wine and beef stock. Add beef back in and cover. Let it come to a boil and then simmer for 2 hours. Then add chopped up potatoes. Let simmer for 1 hour. Enjoy! Let me know what you think if you end up making it ❤️ #irishbeefstew #irishstew #cozyrecipes #comfortfood #healthyrecipes #healthycomfortfood #soupseason #georgiaferrarisrecipes #winterrecipe
